HEADWORD: Gaffle
<hw>Gaf"fle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>geafl</ets> fork, LG., D., Sw., & Dan. <ets>gaffel</ets>, G.
<ets>gabel</ets>, W. <ets>gafl</ets>, Ir. & Gael. <ets>gabhal</ets>. Cf.
<er>Gaff</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An artificial spur or gaff for
